⭐ FULL SUMMARY OF THE VIDEO (Complete, All Points Included)

The video explores the real value and realities of IIT M.Tech in 2025, using evidence from current students, alumni, placement coordinators, and the creator’s own experiences. It reveals both advantages and harsh truths about the IIT tag.

1️⃣ Starting Story — Two Extreme Cases

A Tier-3 student who joined IIT Madras M.Tech (CS) got a Nutanix offer in 20 days.

But another IIT M.Tech alumnus (non-CS) was fired within one year.

Purpose: IIT tag helps, but awareness and skill decide survival.

2️⃣ Current M.Tech Placement Scenario in IITs

A placement coordinator from IIT Bombay explains:

Phase 1 placements (Google, Microsoft, 4 CR packages)

Only a few get in.

Even toppers from non-CS departments struggle because:

They lack programming/AI skills.

Trend: AI is now necessary in resumes

Even CS students with SD or ML skill only are adding SD + AI hybrid resumes.

Companies want AI familiarity across all branches.

3️⃣ Awareness Beats Branch & GATE Rank

Story of Vishnu:

Low GATE score → got into an interdisciplinary dept at IIT Madras.

Took advice from seniors

Chose a professor whose work overlapped coding + ocean engineering.

His M.Tech project → helped him get better packages than many B.Tech students.

Lesson: Awareness and professor selection matter more than branch.

4️⃣ Untold Benefit: Faster Promotion & Higher Entry Level

Story of Shoban:

Tier-3 → M.Tech in interdisciplinary branch at IITM.

Got placed in ICICI.

The grade at which IIT candidates join is 10 years ahead of normal hires.

Promotions are faster and policies better compared to non-IIT hires.

5️⃣ IIT Name Gives Unfair Advantages

Story of Peju (name changed):

Company got sold 2 months after joining.

She applied off-campus → got an interview from Amex despite small projects.

She believes:

“I got the callback because I’m from IIT. Even tier-3 students with better projects get ignored.”

6️⃣ 10 LPA → 85 LPA Jump

An aerospace IITM graduate:

First job: Airbus (10 LPA)

After 1 year → Honda Japan (85 LPA)

Why?

His skills

Plus the IIT tag opening opportunities abroad

7️⃣ Reality: IIT Brand Power Overseas

A student doing M.Tech at IITM:

Only got one call (Honda Japan)

Converted it.

In Japan, he gets special treatment at workplace because of IIT branding.

IIT professors on campus have:

Startups

Big consulting projects

Foreign collaborations

High influence

Some own luxury cars like BMW

